SANTA MONICA, Calif. (AP) _ Lions Gate Entertainment Corp. (LGF.A) on Thursday reported a loss of $104.6 million in its fiscal fourth quarter.The Santa Monica, California-based company said it had a loss of 46 cents per share. Earnings, adjusted for non-recurring costs and stock option expense, were 6 cents per share.The results fell short of Wall Street expectations. The average estimate of five analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for earnings of 9 cents per share.The motion picture producer and distributor posted revenue of $929.9 million in the period, which also fell short of Street forecasts. Seven analysts surveyed by Zacks expected $956.4 million.For the year, the company reported that its loss widened to $188.2 million, or 84 cents per share. Revenue was reported as $3.6 billion._____This story was generated by Automated Insights (http://automatedinsights.com/ap) using data from Zacks Investment Research. Access a Zacks stock report on LGF.A at https://www.zacks.com/ap/LGF.A